{
  "stem": "7093.8",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 146,
      "text": "Because I didn't want to-- I refused to stay with him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 147,
      "text": "And, and then I, I-- and I found I couldn't get new permission to go to Cape Town.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 148,
      "text": "There was no way they'd let me go Cape Town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 149,
      "text": "I had to stay in Durban, because the visa I had, I had only through this job.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 150,
      "text": "And event-- and while I was there, I-- he came to visit me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 151,
      "text": "And every day, he got a little bit better.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 152,
      "text": "And because I saw the he is getting so much better through me, I somehow-- eventually, we moved in together again.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 153,
      "text": "And I became pregnant very soon after.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 154,
      "text": "And on my fifth month of pregnancy-- and he became better and better, until he became a genius, and a Superman, and a god, and then complete breakdown.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 155,
      "text": "And he had to go into mental hospital.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 156,
      "text": "And eventually, he to be certified.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 157,
      "text": "And I had to-- I, I was there without a working permit, without a residence permit, with a baby.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 158,
      "text": "And, and I was at the end of my tether.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 159,
      "text": "I couldn't help him anymore.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 160,
      "text": "If I stayed there, I-- they would have sent him to me to, to-- every time he got a little bit better.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 161,
      "text": "And I just couldn't take it anymore.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 162,
      "text": "I didn't dare to let him near the child, because I was afraid he does something to that child, especially, as when the child was born, he expected a daughter.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 163,
      "text": "And he, he couldn't, he couldn't accept it that it was a son.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 164,
      "text": "And therefore, I was terrified letting the child alone with him even for a minute, because I didn't know what he was going to do.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 165,
      "text": "And, and so I, I went to Israel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 166,
      "text": "I got the Jewish community to pay my trip for Israel.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
